      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I'm looking at some new high-protein kibble for my Lab. He's getting up there in age (around 9) and I'm worried about his weight. What's a good protein-to-fat ratio I should be looking for to keep him healthy but not too heavy?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For your Lab, a good protein-to-fat ratio is crucial, especially as he gets older. You'll want to look for kibble that offers a solid protein content, ideally in the range of 25% to 35% protein. A lower fat content is usually better if you're concerned about weight gain, so aim for a fat percentage below 15%. Always check the ingredient list, and if you're unsure, it's best to consult with your vet.",
